column2: Michael was in the gym and started to become agitated because of
basketball he started telling another student to suck my dick and can't
nobody beat me in this school he then left the gym and I followed
close behind. Then I came into my office for about 5 minutes and as I
open my office door me as well as another CI witnessed Michael
punch another student multiple times. We immediately intervened
and put him in a restraint he kept saying let me up and we told him if
he can be calm and safe we would eventually he did calm down so we
let him go. I then took him to the nurses office so he could be treated
because he was bleeding from a prior sore he had. He was treated
and left the nurses office I followed closely behind because he said he
wanted to get his bike and leave. So when we got to the class where
his bike was his bike wasn't operable so he started asking what
happened to his bike and left the class angry so he started looking for
another student saying where is he I'm bout to kick his ass. I
continued to follow him as he started looking in every classroom
around the building. As we headed over to building 9 he looked in one
of the classrooms and he saw the student he was looking for so the
teacher opened the door he tried to rush in and go after the student
but I was able to grab him and hold him up against the wall until the
teacher could get the student out of the room. After the student left
Michael wanted to leave the room so I let him out and he
immediately tried to go after the other student but once again I
subdued him and he got even more agitated. So I was talking to him
he then appeared calm so as I got a little laxed he ran towards me and
I was unsuccessful when I tried to grab him. Michael ran through the
chute after the other student but in the process knocked down
another student. He spotted the the original student and started
was with a group of students, when one  called another a
bitch.   corrected the other student.  The other student told
him not to tell him what to do.   then attacked the other
student, hitting him numerous times, kneeing him, kicking him.  Then
turned on another student who was trying to get him to stop and
began hitting him too.  Then turned around and returned to hittin the
original student.  When CIs arrived,  swung at this writer.
Myself and Lander moved the student to the floor and implemented a
SCIP 2 person supine.  Moving to the TCI approved Supine when
additional help arrived (Tierney)
The nurse caught Zeke and I in the hall on our way back from the A
hallway bathroom to let us know she needed to see us in her office
and that she had received a call. He was upset and frustrated saying
things like "c'mon man why do they have to search me again?" "I'm
not letting them search me fuck that" However, he walked right to the
nurses office and waited with me until she returned. A CI and a
security officer entered either at the same time as the nurse or
shortly after. As soon as  saw the CI and security officer he
became escalated and started yelling in his seat. He continued to yell
about not wanting to be searched again and that they haven't found
anything and they need to stop going after him and searching him. He
then punched the wall and began to clear paperwork off the small
table in the nurses office and then he started to throw materials
available to him in the room. Other staff in the room at the time
started to clear out potential dangerous items and other students. CI
and security were working on deescalating . I believe he
attempted to leave the nurses office and the door was open. Zeke
tried to push through CI and security to leave. CI and security tried to
contain him and keep him from leaving. I immediately closed the
nurses door when , the CI, and security officer exited the room as
to prevent any other damage or risk to staff and students. This entire
time he was yelling outside the door. It was relayed to me after that
he was restrained in the hallway outside of the nurses office and that
he had spat in the security officers face. Once out of crisis,
returned to the nurses office, was searched and nothing was found
other than a lighter and his backpack clearly smelled of weed. The
nurse checked his vitals and then he was sent back to class to finish
the day.
